text: Ocean City is a town in southeast Maryland. It is near the Atlantic Ocean. The town had 6,844 people as of the 2020 census. Between 320,000 and 345,000 people visit the town every year. The town was founded in 1875. It was incorporated five years later. == References == Category:1875 establishments in the United States Category:1870s establishments in Maryland Category:Towns in Maryland
title: Ocean City, Maryland
